description.narrative: Government, civil society partners, academia, media understand and take action to influence social norms that increase the value of girls/women and promote gender equality ., which contributes to Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. description.narrative: The focus for C4D was to support Government of India’s COVID-19 Vaccine Communication Strategy at the National and State level. The nine modules developed on Communication for Social and Behaviour Change (CSBC) are being adapted for online learning on the UNiLearn platform.;Sections and states were supported with specific gender strategies and gender transformative dialogue. The India Country Office conducted the first-ever Gender Programmatic Review (GPR) through a series of consultations with internal and external stakeholders.;Systematic evidence was conducted through a series of studies and methods to improve both COVID-19 specific and sensitive interventions for all programmes.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/01/2022
